{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":371,"text":"I'm afraid I'm one of those speakers"},{"time":3139,"text":"you hope you're not going to meet at TED."},{"time":6354,"text":"First, I don't have a mobile,"},{"time":7690,"text":"so I'm on the safe side."},{"time":9521,"text":"Secondly, a political theorist"},{"time":11722,"text":"who's going to talk about the crisis of democracy"},{"time":14187,"text":"is probably not the most exciting topic you can think about."},{"time":18259,"text":"And plus, I'm not going to give you any answers."},{"time":20742,"text":"I'm much more trying to add to some of the questions we're talking about."},{"time":24576,"text":"And one of the things that I want to question"},{"time":26742,"text":"is this very popular hope these days"},{"time":29459,"text":"that transparency and openness"},{"time":31393,"text":"can restore the trust in democratic institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35693,"text":"There is one more reason for you to be suspicious about me."},{"time":39409,"text":"You people, the Church of TED, are a very optimistic community."},{"time":43386,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":45594,"text":"Basically you believe in complexity, but not in ambiguity."},{"time":50511,"text":"As you have been told, I'm Bulgarian."},{"time":53426,"text":"And according to the surveys,"},{"time":55010,"text":"we are marked the most pessimistic people in the world."},{"time":58577,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":60361,"text":"The Economist magazine recently wrote an article"},{"time":63951,"text":"covering one of the recent studies on happiness,"},{"time":66502,"text":"and the title was \"The Happy, the Unhappy and the Bulgarians.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":71336,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72936,"text":"So now when you know what to expect,"},{"time":76783,"text":"let's give you the story."},{"time":78219,"text":"And this is a rainy election day in a small country --"},{"time":83170,"text":"that can be my country, but could be also your country."},{"time":86502,"text":"And because of the rain until four o'clock in the afternoon,"},{"time":90302,"text":"nobody went to the polling stations."},{"time":92987,"text":"But then the rain stopped,"},{"time":94752,"text":"people went to vote."},{"time":96986,"text":"And when the votes had been counted,"},{"time":100136,"text":"three-fourths of the people have voted with a blank ballot."},{"time":107452,"text":"The government and the opposition,"},{"time":109802,"text":"they have been simply paralyzed."},{"time":112736,"text":"Because you know what to do about the protests."},{"time":114853,"text":"You know who to arrest, who to negotiate with."},{"time":116837,"text":"But what to do about people who are voting with a blank ballot?"},{"time":122185,"text":"So the government decided to have the elections once again."},{"time":126518,"text":"And this time even a greater number,"},{"time":129068,"text":"83 percent of the people, voted with blank ballots."},{"time":134251,"text":"Basically they went to the ballot boxes"},{"time":137002,"text":"to tell that they have nobody to vote for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140068,"text":"This is the opening of a beautiful novel by Jose Saramago"},{"time":145100,"text":"called \"Seeing.\""},{"time":146583,"text":"But in my view it very well captures"},{"time":148833,"text":"part of the problem that we have with democracy in Europe these days."},{"time":153217,"text":"On one level nobody's questioning"},{"time":155885,"text":"that democracy is the best form of government."},{"time":159784,"text":"Democracy is the only game in town."},{"time":162520,"text":"The problem is that many people start to believe"},{"time":164833,"text":"that it is not a game worth playing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167535,"text":"For the last 30 years, political scientists have observed"},{"time":171833,"text":"that there is a constant decline in electoral turnout,"},{"time":176383,"text":"and the people who are least interested to vote"},{"time":180301,"text":"are the people whom you expect are going to gain most out of voting."},{"time":184938,"text":"I mean the unemployed, the under-privileged."},{"time":188363,"text":"And this is a major issue."},{"time":190055,"text":"Because especially now with the economic crisis,"},{"time":192786,"text":"you can see that the trust in politics,"},{"time":195237,"text":"that the trust in democratic institutions,"},{"time":197819,"text":"was really destroyed."},{"time":199738,"text":"According to the latest survey being done by the European Commission,"},{"time":203354,"text":"89 percent of the citizens of Europe believe that there is a growing gap"},{"time":208236,"text":"between the opinion of the policy-makers and the opinion of the public."},{"time":214562,"text":"Only 18 percent of Italians and 15 percent of Greeks"},{"time":218570,"text":"believe that their vote matters."},{"time":221720,"text":"Basically people start to understand that they can change governments,"},{"time":225786,"text":"but they cannot change policies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228288,"text":"And the question which I want to ask is the following:"},{"time":230904,"text":"How did it happen that we are living in societies"},{"time":234820,"text":"which are much freer than ever before --"},{"time":237370,"text":"we have more rights, we can travel easier,"},{"time":240054,"text":"we have access to more information --"},{"time":242403,"text":"at the same time that trust in our democratic institutions"},{"time":245787,"text":"basically has collapsed?"},{"time":248370,"text":"So basically I want to ask:"},{"time":249806,"text":"What went right and what went wrong in these 50 years"},{"time":254655,"text":"when we talk about democracy?"},{"time":256456,"text":"And I'll start with what went right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260339,"text":"And the first thing that went right was, of course,"},{"time":263401,"text":"these five revolutions which, in my view,"},{"time":265872,"text":"very much changed the way we're living and deepened our democratic experience."},{"time":270456,"text":"And the first was the cultural and social revolution of 1968 and 1970s,"},{"time":275681,"text":"which put the individual at the center of politics."},{"time":278496,"text":"It was the human rights moment."},{"time":280914,"text":"Basically this was also a major outbreak, a culture of dissent,"},{"time":284764,"text":"a culture of basically non-conformism,"},{"time":288630,"text":"which was not known before."},{"time":290931,"text":"So I do believe that even things like that"},{"time":293280,"text":"are very much the children of '68 --"},{"time":296732,"text":"nevertheless that most of us had been even not born then."},{"time":300147,"text":"But after that you have the market revolution of the 1980s."},{"time":303196,"text":"And nevertheless that many people on the left try to hate it,"},{"time":306830,"text":"the truth is that it was very much the market revolution that sent the message:"},{"time":311447,"text":"\"The government does not know better.\""},{"time":313124,"text":"And you have more choice-driven societies."},{"time":316031,"text":"And of course, you have 1989 -- the end of Communism, the end of the Cold War."},{"time":322598,"text":"And it was the birth of the global world."},{"time":324898,"text":"And you have the Internet."},{"time":327030,"text":"And this is not the audience to which I'm going to preach"},{"time":329997,"text":"to what extent the Internet empowered people."},{"time":332414,"text":"It has changed the way we are communicating"},{"time":335247,"text":"and basically we are viewing politics."},{"time":336997,"text":"The very idea of political community totally has changed."},{"time":340015,"text":"And I'm going to name one more revolution,"},{"time":342330,"text":"and this is the revolution in brain sciences,"},{"time":344163,"text":"which totally changed the way"},{"time":346064,"text":"we understand how people are making decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349400,"text":"So this is what went right."},{"time":352364,"text":"But if we're going to see what went wrong,"},{"time":354698,"text":"we're going to end up with the same five revolutions."},{"time":358130,"text":"Because first you have the 1960s and 1970s,"},{"time":361631,"text":"cultural and social revolution,"},{"time":363497,"text":"which in a certain way destroyed the idea of a collective purpose."},{"time":367064,"text":"The very idea, all these collective nouns that we have been taught about --"},{"time":371900,"text":"nation, class, family."},{"time":374697,"text":"We start to like divorcing, if we're married at all."},{"time":377181,"text":"All this was very much under attack."},{"time":380530,"text":"And it is so difficult to engage people in politics"},{"time":384881,"text":"when they believe that what really matters"},{"time":387580,"text":"is where they personally stand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389749,"text":"And you have the market revolution of the 1980s"},{"time":393499,"text":"and the huge increase of inequality in societies."},{"time":399460,"text":"Remember, until the 1970s,"},{"time":401366,"text":"the spread of democracy has always been accompanied"},{"time":405106,"text":"by the decline of inequality."},{"time":408566,"text":"The more democratic our societies have been,"},{"time":410732,"text":"the more equal they have been becoming."},{"time":414765,"text":"Now we have the reverse tendency."},{"time":417099,"text":"The spread of democracy now is very much accompanied"},{"time":419799,"text":"by the increase in inequality."},{"time":421683,"text":"And I find this very much disturbing"},{"time":424917,"text":"when we're talking about what's going on right and wrong"},{"time":428865,"text":"with democracy these days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430749,"text":"And if you go to 1989 --"},{"time":432751,"text":"something that basically you don't expect that anybody's going to criticize --"},{"time":436265,"text":"but many are going to tell you, \"Listen, it was the end of the Cold War"},{"time":440216,"text":"that tore the social contract between the elites and the people in Western Europe.\""},{"time":445516,"text":"When the Soviet Union was still there,"},{"time":447433,"text":"the rich and the powerful, they needed the people,"},{"time":450816,"text":"because they feared them."},{"time":453099,"text":"Now the elites basically have been liberated."},{"time":456400,"text":"They're very mobile. You cannot tax them."},{"time":458565,"text":"And basically they don't fear the people."},{"time":460899,"text":"So as a result of it, you have this very strange situation"},{"time":463916,"text":"in which the elites basically got out of the control of the voters."},{"time":468433,"text":"So this is not by accident"},{"time":469932,"text":"that the voters are not interested to vote anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472918,"text":"And when we talk about the Internet,"},{"time":475032,"text":"yes, it's true, the Internet connected all of us,"},{"time":477533,"text":"but we also know that the Internet created these echo chambers and political ghettos"},{"time":484216,"text":"in which for all your life you can stay with the political community you belong to."},{"time":489318,"text":"And it's becoming more and more difficult"},{"time":491250,"text":"to understand the people who are not like you."},{"time":494016,"text":"I know that many people here"},{"time":495884,"text":"have been splendidly speaking about the digital world and the possibility for cooperation,"},{"time":500648,"text":"but [have you] seen what the digital world has done to American politics these days?"},{"time":504682,"text":"This is also partly a result of the Internet revolution."},{"time":508533,"text":"This is the other side of the things that we like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511199,"text":"And when you go to the brain sciences,"},{"time":513217,"text":"what political consultants learned from the brain scientists"},{"time":517583,"text":"is don't talk to me about ideas anymore,"},{"time":520935,"text":"don't talk to me about policy programs."},{"time":523200,"text":"What really matters is basically to manipulate the emotions of the people."},{"time":528967,"text":"And you have this very strongly"},{"time":531034,"text":"to the extent that, even if you see when we talk about revolutions these days,"},{"time":535435,"text":"these revolutions are not named anymore around ideologies or ideas."},{"time":541434,"text":"Before, revolutions used to have ideological names."},{"time":543900,"text":"They could be communist, they could be liberal,"},{"time":545833,"text":"they could be fascist or Islamic."},{"time":547618,"text":"Now the revolutions are called under the medium which is most used."},{"time":551866,"text":"You have Facebook revolutions, Twitter revolutions."},{"time":555000,"text":"The content doesn't matter anymore, the problem is the media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559400,"text":"I'm saying this because one of my major points"},{"time":561935,"text":"is what went right is also what went wrong."},{"time":566734,"text":"And when we're now trying to see how we can change the situation,"},{"time":570467,"text":"when basically we're trying to see what can be done about democracy,"},{"time":573416,"text":"we should keep this ambiguity in mind."},{"time":575983,"text":"Because probably some of the things that we love most"},{"time":579001,"text":"are going to be also the things that can hurt us most."},{"time":582202,"text":"These days it's very popular to believe"},{"time":585386,"text":"that this push for transparency,"},{"time":587700,"text":"this kind of a combination between active citizens, new technologies"},{"time":594085,"text":"and much more transparency-friendly legislation"},{"time":597749,"text":"can restore trust in politics."},{"time":600817,"text":"You believe that when you have these new technologies and people who are ready to use this,"},{"time":604500,"text":"it can make it much more difficult for the governments to lie,"},{"time":608184,"text":"it's going to be more difficult for them to steal"},{"time":610699,"text":"and probably even going to be more difficult for them to kill."},{"time":614384,"text":"This is probably true."},{"time":616400,"text":"But I do believe that we should be also very clear"},{"time":619450,"text":"that now when we put the transparency at the center of politics"},{"time":624717,"text":"where the message is, \"It's transparency, stupid.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":628316,"text":"Transparency is not about restoring trust in institutions."},{"time":631899,"text":"Transparency is politics' management of mistrust."},{"time":636618,"text":"We are assuming that our societies are going to be based on mistrust."},{"time":641150,"text":"And by the way, mistrust was always very important for democracy."},{"time":643976,"text":"This is why you have checks and balances."},{"time":646116,"text":"This is why basically you have all this creative mistrust"},{"time":650267,"text":"between the representatives and those whom they represent."},{"time":653351,"text":"But when politics is only management of mistrust,"},{"time":658250,"text":"then -- I'm very glad that \"1984\" has been mentioned --"},{"time":661333,"text":"now we're going to have \"1984\" in reverse."},{"time":665083,"text":"It's not going to be the Big Brother watching you,"},{"time":667200,"text":"it's going to be we being the Big Brother"},{"time":669500,"text":"watching the political class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671250,"text":"But is this the idea of a free society?"},{"time":674866,"text":"For example, can you imagine"},{"time":676400,"text":"that decent, civic, talented people are going to run for office"},{"time":682518,"text":"if they really do believe"},{"time":684300,"text":"that politics is also about managing mistrust?"},{"time":688100,"text":"Are you not afraid with all these technologies"},{"time":691134,"text":"that are going to track down"},{"time":693134,"text":"any statement the politicians are going to make on certain issues,"},{"time":696749,"text":"are you not afraid that this is going to be a very strong signal to politicians"},{"time":700616,"text":"to repeat their positions, even the very wrong positions,"},{"time":705250,"text":"because consistency is going to be more important than common sense?"},{"time":709267,"text":"And the Americans who are in the room,"},{"time":710949,"text":"are you not afraid that your presidents are going to govern"},{"time":714001,"text":"on the basis of what they said in the primary elections?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717376,"text":"I find this extremely important,"},{"time":719367,"text":"because democracy is about people changing their views"},{"time":723399,"text":"based on rational arguments and discussions."},{"time":726549,"text":"And we can lose this with the very noble idea"},{"time":730033,"text":"to keep people accountable"},{"time":732049,"text":"for showing the people that we're not going to tolerate"},{"time":734667,"text":"politicians the opportunism in politics."},{"time":737385,"text":"So for me this is extremely important."},{"time":739717,"text":"And I do believe that when we're discussing politics these days,"},{"time":742983,"text":"probably it makes sense"},{"time":745182,"text":"to look also at this type of a story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748584,"text":"But also don't forget, any unveiling is also veiling."},{"time":752134,"text":"[Regardless of] how transparent our governments want to be,"},{"time":755899,"text":"they're going to be selectively transparent."},{"time":758301,"text":"In a small country that could be my country,"},{"time":760333,"text":"but could be also your country,"},{"time":761766,"text":"they took a decision -- it is a real case story --"},{"time":763951,"text":"that all of the governmental decisions,"},{"time":766566,"text":"discussions of the council of ministers,"},{"time":769132,"text":"were going to be published on the Internet"},{"time":772433,"text":"24 hours after the council discussions took place."},{"time":776833,"text":"And the public was extremely all for it."},{"time":779001,"text":"So I had the opportunity to talk to the prime minister,"},{"time":781452,"text":"why he made this decision."},{"time":783050,"text":"He said, \"Listen, this is the best way"},{"time":784766,"text":"to keep the mouths of my ministers closed."},{"time":789394,"text":"Because it's going to be very difficult for them to dissent"},{"time":792479,"text":"knowing that 24 hours after"},{"time":794661,"text":"this is going to be on the public space,"},{"time":796565,"text":"and this is in a certain way going to be a political crisis.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":800511,"text":"So when we talk about transparency,"},{"time":801978,"text":"when we talk about openness,"},{"time":803577,"text":"I really do believe that what we should keep in mind"},{"time":805694,"text":"is that what went right is what went wrong."},{"time":809444,"text":"And this is Goethe, who is neither Bulgarian nor a political scientist,"},{"time":813628,"text":"some centuries ago he said,"},{"time":816110,"text":"\"There is a big shadow where there is much light.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":819447,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820979,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}